</h2>




<h6 class="post-meta">
    Posted by:
    
    <a href="/blog/author/christian/">christian</a>
    
    
    
    
    on 19 Sep 2019
</h6>





<a href="/blog/turning-an-image-into-a-sticker-chart/">
    <img class="img-thumbnail pull-left" src="/static/media/uploads/blog/sticker-chart/.thumbnails/vintage-aircraft_gridded.jpg/vintage-aircraft_gridded-90x90.jpg">
</a>





<p>To produce a children's sticker chart from a provided image, the following code divides it into squares (which can be cut out) and produces further images with matching labels for the reverse side of the printed image and a piece of card onto which the squares can be stuck (you need to provide your own glue).</p>




